e-preserving\naction of a countably infinite amenable group satisfies the measurable version\nof the Lov\\'asz Local Lemma if and only if it admits a factor map to the\n$[0;1]$-shift action. To prove this, we combine the tools of the\nOrnstein--Weiss theory of entropy for actions of amenable groups with concepts\nfrom computability theory, specifically, Kolmogorov complexity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 25 Apr 2016 18:12:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 10 May 2016 23:35:33 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 1 Jul 2016 16:48:02 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Sun, 7 Aug 2016 18:19:45 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Fri, 14 Oct 2016 17:08:25 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Tue, 31 Oct 2017 06:17:26 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Tue, 11 Jun 2019 18:59:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-29"}
