ions dominate the dispersion.\nFinally, the simulated $z \\sim 2-3$ isolated disks and mergers both occupy a\nregion in the \\irxbeta\\ plane consistent with observed $z \\sim 2-3$ dusty\nstar-forming galaxies (DSFGs). Thus, contrary to some claims in the literature,\nthe blue colors of high-z DSFGs do not imply that they are short-lived\nstarbursts.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 25 Apr 2016 20:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 6 Apr 2017 19:08:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-05-10"}
